<p>Hurricane Melissa rapidly intensified into a top-category storm as it moved across the northern Caribbean and was expected to make landfall in Jamaica on Tuesday, bringing the prospect of prolonged, life‑threatening flooding and storm surge . Forecasters warned of extremely heavy rainfall — reports ranged from roughly 30 inches to as much as one metre in some areas — and forecasts stressed the risk of landslides and flash floods for Jamaica, Haiti and the Dominican Republic . Jamaican authorities ordered evacuations for vulnerable coastal and low‑lying areas, and residents and local businesses were taking visible precautions such as covering fuel pumps and moving boats ashore .</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/ssDm0woNpNRkp8iLT7cwNHDHoWi80QxR21BmLPnPZS1XufSqvDJbChIb0zQQ8Fn35AtRBIGEK6lZJH6QzGVVY-eAI5RVcNfYsMj-VU8HBLBQfR_9Y_PYpAUNTjoTV3_iSECvOLyM8SCVdl5rJJ2uJ2nrQZ3ZBVDbNn4wXIJbaqx_nA1E5sJWp0OHlVk3SLAK97a-9aKS0k1jmQKwnznqAw' alt='Fishermen in Port Royal, Jamaica, preparing for Hurricane Melissa on Sunday.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Peak wind forecasts: Some model runs and forecasts put peak winds near 160 mph, which would place Melissa among the strongest storms to directly strike Jamaica if realized</li><li>Local preparations: Jamaica issued mandatory evacuations for vulnerable zones including parts of Kingston, and images show people covering fuel pumps and fishermen preparing vessels ahead of the storm</li><li>Rapid intensification: Meteorologists said Melissa underwent a period of rapid intensification over the weekend, accelerating its climb up the Saffir‑Simpson scale and complicating forecasts</li><li>Regional exposure: Beyond Jamaica, officials warned that southern Haiti, the Dominican Republic and parts of Cuba could face torrents, flash flooding and landslides from Melissa&#x27;s outer bands</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Government of Jamaica: Officials ordered mandatory evacuations for vulnerable and low‑lying areas, including parts of Kingston, to protect residents from flooding and storm surge. (<a href='https://www.theguardian.com/world/2025/oct/26/hurricane-melissa-strengthens-into-category-4-approaches-jamaica'>The Guardian</a>)</li><li>U.S. National Hurricane Center / U.S. forecasters: Forecasters warned Melissa could produce life‑threatening flash flooding, dangerous storm surge and very heavy rainfall across the northern Caribbean. (<a href='https://www.npr.org/2025/10/27/g-s1-95164/melissa-category-5-hurricane'>NPR</a>)</li><li>Local residents / fishermen: People in coastal communities were preparing boats and supplies and taking visible protective measures as the storm approached. (<a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2025/10/26/world/americas/hurricane-melissa-caribbean-rain-flood.html'>The New York Times</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2025/10/26/world/americas/hurricane-melissa-caribbean-rain-flood.html'>Caribbean Braces for Hurricane Melissa</a> - nytimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/10/27/jamaica-braces-as-hurricane-melissa-strengthens-offshore'>Jamaica braces as Hurricane Melissa strengthens offshore</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.theglobeandmail.com/world/video-melissa-strengthens-into-category-4-hurricane-as-it-approaches-jamaica/'>Melissa strengthens into Category 4 hurricane as it approaches Jamaica, Haiti</a> - theglobeandmail.com</li><li><a href='https://www.npr.org/2025/10/27/g-s1-95164/melissa-category-5-hurricane'>Melissa strengthens to a Category 5 hurricane as it nears Jamaica</a> - npr.org</li><li><a href='https://www.abc.net.au/news/2025-10-27/melissa-strengthens-into-category-5-hurricane/105937990'>Hurricane Melissa strengthens as it approaches Jamaica</a> - abc.net.au</li><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/Melissa-a-Category-4-hurricane-as-Jamaica-braces-for-impact'>Melissa a Category 4 hurricane as Jamaica braces for impact</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='htt